  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 290.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then came Izabella, who was [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] known as Baby [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and in the family was, was called Madame Drama, because she had this dramatic flair, which she has retained for, for all her life.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She's a, indeed, a very dramatic personality and, and incidentally, was not only dramatic in, in the sense of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] being very attractive.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She's extremely beautiful and [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] impressive, but she always wanted to be an actress and was fairly well-known in town for her impersonation of all sorts of actresses, particularly Joan Crawford.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And she has retained that, that dramatic flair in, in everything, in her appearance.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She can write a postcard and it, it's a big drama on a small postcard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then came my sister Regina, who is R-E-G-I-N-A, and who was generally known by her Hebrew name with a diminutive.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We either called her [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Rivka ?] or [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Rivkala, ?] usually.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She, she was the only one who managed to go to junior high and-- but could never finish, because she was thrown out as a Jew in 1944 or '43.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I don't really remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She, too, was interested in being an actress.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I think I've shown you a picture of one of the plays that she has participated in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And incidentally, I should tell you that my sister Berta was at one time considered one of the potentially great poetesses of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And, and interestingly enough, she ceased to write when she came to, to the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The change of language and culture apparently-- and apparently, you know, robbed her of, of the, the vehicle to express herself, on the one hand.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
